# Copy to `.env` and fill in. `.env` is gitignored.

# ── Writing projects (the /words stories) ─────────────────────────────
# PRIMARY (Workers): the R2 bucket is read via the `STORIES` binding in
# wrangler.jsonc (bucket pauldoldendotcom-cdn) — no env var, no public URL.
#
# This var is the OPTIONAL fallback for environments without the binding
# (e.g. a non-Workers host): a base URL serving the bucket over HTTPS.
# Server-only — NO `VITE_` prefix; read inside the server functions.
# No binding and no URL → the app falls back to the in-repo sample (empty).
#
# Object layout (same for the binding and the URL):
#   catalog.json               -> { "stories": [ { id, title, status, coverColor,
#                                   blurb, logline, tags, words, progress, published,
#                                   toc: [ { index, title, date, words, isNew?, published } ] } ] }
#   <storyId>/<index>.md       -> the chapter body, authored in Markdown
#
# `published` (story + per chapter) is the visibility flag: the public site
# shows only published items; everything else is a draft. Managed from the
# /words/admin uploader — you don't normally hand-edit catalog.json.
#
# Chapter Markdown supports `:::` directives for the LitRPG interludes:
#   :::system tone=gold icon=▲ title="LEVEL UP"
#   You reached **Level 24**.
#   :::
#   :::quote cite="Rue, ch. 42"
#   The System doesn't care what you wanted.
#   :::
#   :::skill name="Emberstep" kind="Active · Hex" rarity=legendary tier="Tier I" cost="40 MP" cooldown="12s"
#   Step through the veil for 4 seconds.
#   :::
# Plus normal Markdown: paragraphs (first gets a drop cap), **bold**, *italic*, `code`, [links](url).
#
# STORIES_R2_BASE_URL=https://stories.pauldolden.com

# ── Admin uploader (/words/admin) — Cloudflare Access ─────────────────
# The uploader is gated by Cloudflare Access at the edge; the write API also
# verifies the Access JWT (src/server/access.ts). These are NON-secret public
# identifiers and live in wrangler.jsonc `vars` for prod — listed here only as
# reference. Localhost `vite dev` BYPASSES Access (no edge in front).
#   CF_ACCESS_TEAM_DOMAIN=https://<team>.cloudflareaccess.com
#   CF_ACCESS_AUD=<Access application Audience (AUD) tag>
#   ADMIN_EMAILS=pauldolden@gmail.com   # comma-separated allowlist
